GRANTING ACCESS:
vi /opt/tomcat9/webapps/manager/META-INF/context.xml

Use a multi line comment (<!--    -->) to comment the lines valve...127

CONFIGURE USER:
vi /opt/tomcat9/conf/tomcat-users.xml

add a line in the <tomcat-users> tag;

add the lines below to create a user: 
<user username = "userName" password = "passWord" roles = "manager-gui, admin-gui"/> 

Note: Make sure not to paste this line in the commented section.

CHANGING THE PORT NUMBER
Default port is 8080, 

vi /opt/tomcat9/conf/server.xml

HOT FIXES 

vi /opt/tomcat9/webapps/jsps/jsps

GRANT PASSWORD AUTHENTICATION

sudo vi /etc/ssh/sshd_config

then, change PasswordAuthentication from "no" to "yes"


